snippet.textDisplay:
(Massive Spoiler Warning!)

So, you cannot wield the force unless you have "royal" blood? This movie was a giant "Fuck You" to Kylo Ren.

Daisy Ridley - a fantastic actor - was just the wrong choice for this. Keira Knightly look-alikes alone are a cause for hate.

Relationship development seriously needed between Kylo and Rey... 4 or 5 shocker moments seemed like desperation trying to cover up loose ends. Where did Snope come from? What was Palpatine doing and HOW - when he electrocuted all those ships? Kylo Ren dies and moments later Rey is laughing with her friends? The force? No thanks!

Graphics/Special effects were fantastic, but at the expense of plot gravitas.

Going to fan-fiction to hopefully get an alternate ending that makes more sense and will be far more satisfying.

The plot plays into all the established cliche's that no amount of clever humor can cover.

Cancelling my tickets to Anaheim.

snippet.textDisplay: Star Wars fans don't know what they want; George Lucas was criticized for the way he made the prequels, which looked better technology in the past than in the times of episode 4, 5 and 6, that the plot was boring and with very little action. Now that Disney has it, they cry because it's missing an epic creation. When in reality it is the same fanatics that edged their creator to detach himself from his creation. I'm sorry to say this, but the fans propitiated this. You reap what you sow. They attacked Lucas to exhaustion and now they cannot help missing what would have been if he had directed the final trilogy of this once adored and now hated trilogy. And to be honest, I love episodes 1, 2 and 3; despite Jar Jar Binks. In the first movie, intrigues and corruptions are observed within the governments of the republic, that is, little action and much talk. In the second film the consequences of this bureaucracy are observed, war is unleashed. And in the third it looks like the ignorance and opulence of the Jedi led them to their near extinction. These plots were perfect and perfect for the first 4, 5 and 6. With Disney we saw in episodoo 7, an episode 4 version 2.1, an episode 8 as episode 5 2.2 and now a rehash of episode 7, to please the fans. J.J. Abrams and Ryan were not up to George Lucas and his visión.
